                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the Secretary of
                        Labor</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-16">September 16,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the Secretary of Labor</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Prime Minister seemed wholly favorable to a calling of the meeting by the
                        <gloss target="#t_ILO1">I.L.O.</gloss> The place suggested was Montreal. I
                    see no reason, therefore, why you should not go ahead with it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
